section.def:
passenger
                (乘客) does not include the spouse or child of a
            member of the crew travelling with him;

suitable
                (適合), in relation to material, means approved by
            the Authority as suitable for the purpose for which it is used;

paragraph.content:
all structures, furniture and fittings, and the means of access to and
                    egress from the crew accommodation, shall be so situated, constructed and
                    arranged as to minimize any risk of injury to the crew;

subparagraph.content:
handrails shall be provided in passageways and stairways where
                        necessary and shall be of robust construction and strongly secured to
                        bulkheads;

in ships of under
                        3
                        000 tons, 3.75 square metres;

in ships of under
                        3
                        000 tons, 2.75 square metres;

paragraph.content:
an adequate flush of water which shall always be available and supplied
                    through self-closing non-concussive supply valves with a portable seating of
                    metal which is not likely to become corroded;

a separate room containing a water closet and a washbasin within or near to
                    the engine room control compartment or, in ships not fitted with such a
                    compartment, within easy access of the propelling machinery space;

suitable sinks or washing machines which may be installed in washrooms if
                    provision of a separate laundry facility is not reasonably practicable, with an
                    adequate supply of hot and cold fresh water or means of heating water;

section.def:
sleeping
                room
                (寢室) does not include a hospital ward;

steamer
                (汽船) includes a ship propelled by electricity or
            other mechanical power;

paragraph.content:
a vessel authorized by virtue of a passenger certificate and general safety
                certificate issued under Part II of the Merchant Shipping (Safety) Ordinance (Cap. 369) to carry passengers within river trade limits;
                or

subsection.def:
Part I ship (第I部船舶) means a ship to which Part I and Schedules 1,
                    2, 3, 4 and 5 apply under
                    section 3;

shipowner (船東) has
                the meaning given by section 2(1) of the Working and Living Conditions
                Regulation;

paragraph.content:
if it covers a deck exposed to the weather, provide thermal insulation
                        not less than that provided by a wooden deck 57 millimetres thick;
                        or

subsection.content:
if laid in a permanent hospital, be such that it will not be readily
                    susceptible to damage by liquids which are likely to be used in the
                    hospital;

subparagraph.content:
every point mid-way between any lamp and any position on the boundary
                        of that space to which that lamp is nearer than any other lamp;
                        and

paragraph.content:
chain pipes, and ventilator trunks to cargo spaces or tanks, shall be
                        made of steel or other suitable material and shall be gastight where they
                        pass through any part of the crew accommodation;

there shall be no direct opening between the crew accommodation (other
                        than recreation deck spaces) and any space used as a store room for engine
                        room stores or deck department stores;

Comfortable seats sufficient to accommodate at one time all the
                        seafarers accommodated in the room. Such seats shall be provided in addition
                        to the beds in the room;

For each seafarer accommodated in the room a second drawer having a
                        capacity of at least 2 cubic feet shall be provided in addition to the
                        drawer referred to in subsection (1)(a);

in the case of a bath and shower combined, hot and cold fresh water
                        shall be required to be laid on only to the bath or the shower;
                        and

an adequate flush of water, which shall be always available and
                        supplied through self-closing non-concussive supply valves with a portable
                        seating in metal which is not likely to become corroded;

an arrangement which automatically flushes the pan at intervals not
                        exceeding 5 minutes and provides a continuous trickle of water;
                        and

a clothes locker additional to that required by subsection (13) and
                        complying with the specifications set forth in section
                            15(1)(a)(ii);
